ğŸ›‘What are the storage classes in GCP Cloud Storage?
1)Standard Storage â†’ For frequently accessed data (hot data).Example: Real-time apps, websites.
2)Nearline Storage â†’ For data accessed once a month.Example: Backups, disaster recovery.
3)Coldline Storage â†’ For data accessed once a quarter (very infrequent).Example: Archival with occasional access.
4)Archive Storage â†’ For data accessed once a year or less (long-term archival).Example: Compliance records, medical/legal data.
