âœ… Explanation: How to Create a GCS Bucket (in Console)
1 Go to GCS Console
Open https://console.cloud.google.com/storage/browser

2 Click â€œCreate bucketâ€

3 Give a globally unique bucket name
  Example: my_bkt_name9640
  Bucket names must be unique across all of Google Cloud.
  
4 Choose the Location Type and Location
  Location type: Regional or Multi-region
  Location: For example, us-central1, asia-south1, etc.
  
5 Choose a Storage Class
  Options: Standard, Nearline, Coldline, or Archive
  Example: Select Standard (commonly used)
  
6 Set Access Control
  Choose Uniform (recommended for most cases)
  Or choose Fine-grained if you want object-level permissions
  
7 (Optional) Configure:
  Encryption
  Retention policies
  Labels
  
8 Click â€œCreateâ€
 âœ… Your bucket is now ready to use!
