What is Composer? 
Cloud Composer is a fully managed workflow orchestration service in Google Cloud.
It is based /built on Apache Airflow (an open-source platform) designed for  

âœ…Creating:-You write a Python script called a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph),In that script, you list tasks (like load data, run query, send email) and their order.
âœ…Scheduling :-	Set daily, hourly, or custom execution schedules
âœ…Managing   :-	No need to install or manage Airflow servers yourself
âœ…Monitoring complex workflows:--Get logs, retry failed tasks, set alerts

âœ… Common use cases for Cloud Composer include:---  
Data processing pipelines, scheduling 
ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) workflows,  
Automation of routine tasks. 
Infrastructure Automation 
